                <article class="full-article gp">
                    <header>
                        <h1 class="article-title" itemprop="headline">Church in Wales shows support for same sex marriage</h1>
                        <div class="byline">
                          <span>
                                <a class="reporter link" href="/reporter/ruth-gledhill">
                                  <meta itemprop="jobTitle" content="Company Name Contributor">
                                  <span itemprop="name">Ruth Gledhill</span>
                                </a>
                          </span>
                        <time datetime="17 September 2015 | 10:32 PM" itemprop="datePublished dateModified">17 September 2015 | 10:32 PM</time>
                        </div>
                       <div class="shareline">
    <span class="btn-fblike"><iframe class="iframe-fblike" src="https://www.facebook.com/plugins/like.php?href=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.facebook.com%2FChristianTodayInternational&width=62&layout=button&action=like&size=large&show_faces=false&share=false&height=65&appId=805996846250933" width="62" height="28" style="border:none;overflow:hidden" scrolling="no" frameborder="0" allowTransparency="true" allow="encrypted-media"></iframe></span>
    <a class="icon facebook"  href="https://www.facebook.com/sharer.php?u=https://www.christiantoday.com/article/church-in-wales-shows-support-for-same-sex-marriage/65061.htm" aria-label="Share on Facebook"  target="_blank"><span class="i-wp"><svg width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 800 800" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"><path fill="currentColor" d="M445 643h-90V419h-75v-87h75v-64q0-55 32-86 30-29 80-29 28 0 67 3v78h-47q-42 0-42 38v60h86l-11 87h-75v224z"/></svg></span></a>
    <a class="icon twitter"   href="https://twitter.com/intent/tweet?url=https://www.christiantoday.com/article/church-in-wales-shows-support-for-same-sex-marriage/65061.htm&text=Church in Wales shows support for same sex marriage" aria-label="Share on Twitter"   target="_blank"><span class="i-wp"><svg width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 800 800" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"><path fill="currentColor" d="M679 239s-21 34-55 57c7 156-107 329-314 329-103 0-169-50-169-50s81 17 163-45c-83-5-103-77-103-77s23 6 50-2c-93-23-89-110-89-110s23 14 50 14c-84-65-34-148-34-148s76 107 228 116c-22-121 117-177 188-101 37-6 71-27 71-27s-12 41-49 61c30-2 63-17 63-17z"/></svg></span></a>
    <a class="icon pinterest" href="https://www.pinterest.com/pin/create/button/?url=https://www.christiantoday.com/article/church-in-wales-shows-support-for-same-sex-marriage/65061.htm" aria-label="Share on Pinterest" target="_blank"><span class="i-wp"><svg width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 800 800" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"><path fill="currentColor" d="M287 681c-9-3-15-77-6-115l38-163s-9-20-9-49c0-46 26-80 59-80 28 0 42 21 42 46 0 28-19 71-28 110-8 33 17 59 49 59 58 0 104-61 104-150 0-79-57-134-138-134-94 0-148 69-148 142 0 28 9.7 57.4 23 74 4 5 5 6 2 17l-8 31s-2 9.5-14 3c-41-22.3-63-78-63-126 0-104 75-199 217-199 114 0 203 81 203 190 0 113-72 205-171 205-55 0-75-38-75-38l-21 78c-11 41-47 102-56 99z"/></svg></span></a>
</div>
                    </header>
                    <p><p>The Anglican&nbsp;<a title="Church in Wales" href="http://www.churchinwales.org.uk" target="_blank">Church In Wales</a>&nbsp;took the first steps towards allowing clergy to celebrate same sex marriage in its churches when more than half its Governing Body voted in favour of the move.</p>
<p>A secret ballot in Lampeter, Ceredigion showed that just over half, 61 out of 120 members, were in favour of&nbsp;change. Much more support would be needed for a change to take effect, however, and a bill would have to be brought to the Governing Body by the bishops.</p>
<div class="relatedArticle"><div class="label">Related</div><ul><li><a href="https://www.christiantoday.com/article/two.thirds.of.republicans.oppose.gay.marriage.ruling.by.supreme.courtpoll/58515.htm" target="_blank">Two-thirds of Republicans oppose gay marriage ruling by Supreme Court—poll</a></li><li><a href="https://www.christiantoday.com/article/episcopal.church.confirms.change.in.law.to.allow.same.sex.marriages/57833.htm" target="_blank">Episcopal Church confirms change in law to allow same-sex marriages</a></li><li><a href="https://www.christiantoday.com/article/ireland.same.sex.marriage.vote.catholic.church.needs.a.reality.check.says.archbishop/54560.htm" target="_blank">Ireland same sex marriage vote: Catholic Church needs a 'reality check', says Archbishop</a></li></ul></div>
<p>The Church in Wales leadership is concerned that it responds to gay couples seeking to marry with more sensitivity than it did in the past to divorcees wanting a second marriage in church. A <a title="Church in Wales paper on same sex marriage" href="http://cinw.s3.amazonaws.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/13_02_SameSexPartnershipNote.pdf" target="_blank">background note</a>&nbsp;about informal discussions on the issue&nbsp;states that Governing Body&nbsp;<span style="line-height: 20px;">members are "keen that the Church should be able to respond to same sex couples with more pastoral sensitivity than might have been the case in the past when dealing with remarried divorcees. Some members were clearly uncomfortable with the concept of same sex marriage, but others appeared to be open to the possibility of blessing such unions."</span></p>
<figure class="center"><img class="imgPhoto  full" layout="responsive" src="https://christiantoday-4cf9.kxcdn.com/en/full/17510/church-in-wales-governing-body.jpg?w=760&h=507&l=37&t=39" height="507" width="760" /><figcaption class="caption"> The Church in Wales Governing Body took a straw poll on same-sex marriage</figcaption></figure>
<p><span style="line-height: 20px;">If the Governing Body were to take a formal vote for the change in future, the Marriage Act of 2013 which introduced same sex marriage to England and Wales would then be amended to allow the Church in Wales to perform same-sex marriages. The Episcopal Church in Scotland voted recently to begin moving towards same-sex marriage. Some bishops in Ireland support it but there are no plans to introduce same-sex marriage to Northern Ireland at present so change there is unlikely. The Church of England leadership is adamantly opposed and no change is expected in the forseeable future. The US Episcopal Church authorised a change in its laws in July this year.</span></p>
<p>The Archbishop of Wales, Dr Barry Morgan, <a title="Church in Wales and same sex marriage" href="http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-wales-mid-wales-34278101" target="_blank">told the BBC</a>&nbsp;that it is now up to the Bench of Bishops to decide how to take it forward.&nbsp;Then it will be for the governing body to pass a bill. He said:&nbsp;"It is quite a long convoluted complicated process."&nbsp;</p></p>                    <div class="shareline">
    <span class="btn-fblike"><iframe class="iframe-fblike" src="https://www.facebook.com/plugins/like.php?href=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.facebook.com%2FChristianTodayInternational&width=62&layout=button&action=like&size=large&show_faces=false&share=false&height=65&appId=805996846250933" width="62" height="28" style="border:none;overflow:hidden" scrolling="no" frameborder="0" allowTransparency="true" allow="encrypted-media"></iframe></span>
    <a class="icon facebook"  href="https://www.facebook.com/sharer.php?u=https://www.christiantoday.com/article/church-in-wales-shows-support-for-same-sex-marriage/65061.htm" aria-label="Share on Facebook"  target="_blank"><span class="i-wp"><svg width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 800 800" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"><path fill="currentColor" d="M445 643h-90V419h-75v-87h75v-64q0-55 32-86 30-29 80-29 28 0 67 3v78h-47q-42 0-42 38v60h86l-11 87h-75v224z"/></svg></span></a>
    <a class="icon twitter"   href="https://twitter.com/intent/tweet?url=https://www.christiantoday.com/article/church-in-wales-shows-support-for-same-sex-marriage/65061.htm&text=Church in Wales shows support for same sex marriage" aria-label="Share on Twitter"   target="_blank"><span class="i-wp"><svg width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 800 800" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"><path fill="currentColor" d="M679 239s-21 34-55 57c7 156-107 329-314 329-103 0-169-50-169-50s81 17 163-45c-83-5-103-77-103-77s23 6 50-2c-93-23-89-110-89-110s23 14 50 14c-84-65-34-148-34-148s76 107 228 116c-22-121 117-177 188-101 37-6 71-27 71-27s-12 41-49 61c30-2 63-17 63-17z"/></svg></span></a>
